e we have customers, and during \"off\" times, this role will travel to the Park City office to assist the team there. This is a full-time position with benefits that include paid time-off, sick leave, paid holidays, health and supplemental insurance, stock options, and 401(k). Compensation will be commensurate with experience. No relocation package is available. Some remote work is possible for a candidate who is able to prioritize their own tasks and deliver results with minimal supervision. Travel is likely. This role will be advertised under several different titles and job descriptions in order to identify candidates using \"database marketing techniques\" that require us to match the text that you type into the search engine. To apply for this role, please complete the Candidate Survey Application here: https://forms.gle/R5CYA8Lti4Ut7EKD9 ----- This role focuses on providing sales engineering assistance to our sales team and partners. Responsibilities can include site walks, provisioning services, technical support and relationship management with our rapidly growing list of partners. You can also expect to do on-site programming of new installations, reprogramming existing systems, remote diagnostics, troubleshooting and repairing malfunctioning systems. JOB DESCRIPTION What you\u2019ll be responsible for... Pre-Installation Coordination: Stage and pre-commission lighting control systems to facilitate easier/faster onsite provisioning. Sales Assistance: Assist sales team with partner (ESCO, agents, and OEMs) relationship support. Provide in person and phone support for hardware specifications, project quoting and questions. Fixture Testing and Validation: Work with lighting manufacturers to spec and test new fixtures which can be added to Avi-on\u2019s extensive list of supported fixtures. Project Quoting and Take Offs: Using Bluebeam, cut sheets and sales support material provide submittals and project quotes to partners. Project Coordination and Management: Using workflow management tools like ClickUp to ensure that supplies, people, and partners are on site at the proper times to achieve a quick, successful installation experience. Customer Engagement: Help develop and grow partnerships through direct timely engagement with ESCO project quoting staff and project specifiers. Field Feedback: Documenting field input on issues, features, and product requirements into development systems to ensure that action is taken. Periodically: On-site Provisioning: Perform programming of wireless lighting control/digital lighting systems, troubleshooting and repairing malfunctioning systems, provide system training to end user. On-site Coordination: Maintain daily communications with contractors and end users to ensure schedule alignment, proper follow-up, and resolution to punch list items, delivering superior customer satisfaction. Post-Installation Job Reporting: Complete accurate and timely \u201cAs-Programmed\u201d service logs. Customer Support Material: You\u2019ll work with the product and marketing teams to create technical and qualitative content to nurture relationships and add value. About you\u2026 You enjoy using being an expert at software and hardware solutions to deliver a successful result for the partner and customer. IT is second nature to you. You have a professional presence, both online and in person, that allows you to build trust and nurture relationships. You are a skilled listener and communication, able to measure and manage temperament of installer, partner, and end customer. You are hands-on, multi-tasking, collaborative and can successfully engage with cross-functional teams in a culture where colleagues pitch in to help each other succeed. You have strong technical skills and can quickly master Avi-on Software and Hardware platforms, allowing you to discover and demonstrate value to prospective customers. Requirements: Ability to work independently, and methodically problem solve, often onsite at customer job site. Enjoy working with (and de-bugging) wireless products, routers, and other technical details that make IOT products work. Strong Project Management skills, attention to detail, and ability to manage multiple projects/delivery schedules at a given time. Enjoys mastering digital and mobile project management tools to keep everyone informed. Demonstrates strong verbal and written communication skills and has a passion for taking care of the customer. Enjoys writing and writes well. Both personal and professional interest and hands-on experience in lighting, wiring, electronics, and automation. (You can talk volts, amps, watts, loads, and resistors.) Note: Please provide a cover letter that illustrates both your writing abilities and your understanding of the lighting and/or lighting controls industry. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS: 3+ years of Field Service experience with networked systems or related experience Associates or Bachelor\u2019s Degree in Electronics, Electrical/Computer/Mechanical Engineering, or similar. This role reports to Director of Customer Delivery, and takes additional direction from other management team members. The position is located in Park City, Utah. Travel varies with business needs but could be up to 80%. Compensation will be commensurate with experience, and it will include a stock option plan. Avi-on reserves the right to adjust the title of the role based on actual experience and changing organizational needs. Next Steps Note: Please provide a cover letter and resume that illustrates both your writing abilities and your understanding of the lighting and/or lighting controls industry. Job Type: Full-time Benefits: 401(k) Dental Insurance Disability Insurance Health Insurance Life Insurance Paid Time Off Vision Insurance Schedule: Monday to Friday COVID-19 considerations: Avi-on is following local health orders regarding COVID-19. As a technology company, we have plenty of remote productivity tools. As the crisis passes, we will expect you to either be on a customer site or report to the Park City office. Experience: wireless controls: 1 year (Preferred) field sales or services engineering: 1 year (Preferred) lighting controls or lighting industry: 1 year (Preferred) Construction Management: 1 year (Preferred) lighting industry: 3 years (Preferred) technical writing: 1 year (Preferred) Education: Bachelor's (Preferred) Location: Park City, UT 84098 (Preferred) Work authorization: United States (Preferred) Additional Compensation: Other forms Company's website: avi-on.com Benefit Conditions: Waiting period may apply Only full-time employees eligible Work Remotely: Temporarily due to COVID-19 "
